# Student 5 — Phase 2 + Phase 3 (Image Captioning)

**Assignment**: DL AT3 — VizWiz Image Captioning
**Axis explored**: Bahdanau (additive) vs. Luong (multiplicative) attention, with encoder, decoder cell type, hidden size, optimiser, and schedule held constant.

| Phase | Model | Config |
|---|---|---|
| 2 | ViT-B/16 + GRU + Luong attention | `configs/models/s5_m1_vit_gru_luong.yaml` |
| 3 | ViT-B/16 + GRU + Bahdanau attention | `configs/models/s5_m2_vit_gru_bahdanau.yaml` |

All heavy lifting is in `src/`; this notebook is orchestration. See `plan.md` at the project root for the full group plan, evaluation protocol, and 4-student differentiation matrix.

## § 1 — Imports, config, seeding, device
import os, sys, json
from pathlib import Path
import torch
import yaml

if not Path("src").is_dir() and Path("../src").is_dir():
    os.chdir("..")
sys.path.insert(0, ".")

from src import (
    Vocabulary, load_config, set_seed, set_plot_style,
    DataLoaders, Trainer, build_captioner,
    count_parameters, pretty_print_metrics,
    plot_qualitative_samples, plot_training_curves, plot_grpo_curves,
    plot_caption_lengths_compared,
    plot_metric_heatmap,
    parameter_breakdown_table, hyperparameter_summary_table,
    metrics_table_6block, architecture_comparison_table,
    prediction_diff_table, caption_length_stats_table,
)

DATA_CFG = load_config("configs/data_config.yaml")
set_seed(DATA_CFG.seed)
DEVICE = torch.device("cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu")
set_plot_style()

## § 2 — Load Phase-1 artifacts and sanity-check
PROCESSED = Path("data/processed")
vocab = Vocabulary.load(PROCESSED / "vocab.json")
summary = json.loads((PROCESSED / "data_prep_summary.json").read_text(encoding="utf-8"))
assert summary["vocab_size"] == len(vocab), "vocab/summary mismatch — re-run Phase 1 data prep"
print(f"Vocab size: {len(vocab)}  specials: pad={vocab.pad_idx} start={vocab.start_idx} "
      f"end={vocab.end_idx} unk={vocab.unk_idx}")
print(f"Split sizes (images): train={summary['counts']['split']['train_images']}  "
      f"val={summary['counts']['split']['val_images']}  "
      f"test={summary['counts']['split']['test_images']}")

## § 3 — Build DataLoaders

`train` / `val_cap` use `VizWizCaptionDataset` (per-caption rows, for cross-entropy training).
`val_eval` / `test_eval` use `VizWizEvalDataset` (per-image rows with reference captions, for BLEU/CIDEr/ROUGE).
CFG_M1 = yaml.safe_load(Path("configs/models/s5_m1_vit_gru_luong.yaml").read_text(encoding="utf-8"))
loaders_m1 = DataLoaders.from_config(CFG_M1, DATA_CFG, DEVICE)
print(loaders_m1)
imgs, caps, lens, ids = next(iter(loaders_m1.train))
print(f"train batch: imgs={tuple(imgs.shape)}  caps={tuple(caps.shape)}  lens[:8]={lens[:8].tolist()}")

## § 4 — Model 1 rationale
**Phase 2 (Model 1): ViT-B/16 (frozen) + GRU decoder with Luong (multiplicative) attention.**

ImageNet-pretrained ViT-B/16 supplies 196 patch tokens at 768-dim (last 3 transformer blocks unfrozen); a single-layer GRU decoder cross-attends with Luong's multiplicative formulation, $\text{score}(h_t, \bar h_s) = h_t^\top W_a \bar h_s$. This establishes the multiplicative-attention baseline for the controlled comparison in Phase 3 — fewer parameters than Bahdanau and well-suited to GPU matmul.

## § 5 — Model 1 build, parameter count, forward sanity
RUN_DIR_M1 = Path("outputs") / CFG_M1["run_name"]
RUN_DIR_M1.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
(RUN_DIR_M1 / "config.yaml").write_text(yaml.safe_dump(CFG_M1), encoding="utf-8")

model_m1 = build_captioner(CFG_M1, vocab).to(DEVICE)
print(f"Model 1 ({CFG_M1['run_name']})")
print(f"  trainable / total params: "
      f"{count_parameters(model_m1, True)/1e6:.2f}M / {count_parameters(model_m1, False)/1e6:.2f}M")

with torch.no_grad():
    imgs, caps, lens, _ = next(iter(loaders_m1.train))
    logits = model_m1(imgs.to(DEVICE), caps.to(DEVICE), lens.to(DEVICE))
print(f"  logits shape: {tuple(logits.shape)}  (expect [B, T-1, V] with V={len(vocab)})")
assert logits.shape[-1] == len(vocab)

display(parameter_breakdown_table(model_m1).style
        .background_gradient(subset=["trainable_M"], cmap="Blues")
        .format({"params_M": "{:.3f}", "trainable_M": "{:.3f}", "trainable_%": "{:.1f}"}))
display(hyperparameter_summary_table(CFG_M1))
## § 6 — Model 1 training

`fit(...)` (Lightning/sklearn-style orchestrator) handles the full loop: optimiser + scheduler + AMP,
val metrics each epoch, `best.pt` overwritten when val CIDEr improves. No early stop — the full
training curve is preserved for the report (following Liang 2025's fixed-epoch schedule).
trainer_m1 = Trainer(CFG_M1, model_m1, loaders_m1, vocab, DEVICE, RUN_DIR_M1)
trainer_m1.fit()                                  # Stage 1 CE → best.pt
trainer_m1.fit_grpo()                             # Stage 2 GRPO RL → best_grpo.pt

## § 7 — Model 1 test-split evaluation

Reloads `best.pt`, runs greedy + beam decoding, computes BLEU-1..4 + CIDEr + ROUGE-L, writes
`outputs/<run>/metrics.json` and `predictions_test.json`.
# Writes 4 blocks (greedy/beam × CE/GRPO) into metrics.json + predictions_test.json.
# Return values discarded — downstream cells re-read from disk so the notebook is
# kernel-restart safe.
trainer_m1.evaluate_on_test(checkpoint="ce")
trainer_m1.evaluate_on_test(checkpoint="grpo")

m1_metrics = json.loads((RUN_DIR_M1 / "metrics.json").read_text(encoding="utf-8"))
print(pretty_print_metrics(m1_metrics["beam"],
                           f"Model 1 CE test — BEAM (size {CFG_M1['eval']['beam_size']})"))
print()
print(pretty_print_metrics(m1_metrics["grpo_beam"],
                           f"Model 1 CE→GRPO test — BEAM (size {CFG_M1['eval']['beam_size']})"))

m1_metrics = json.loads((RUN_DIR_M1 / "metrics.json").read_text(encoding="utf-8"))
display(metrics_table_6block({
    "greedy":       m1_metrics.get("greedy"),
    "beam":         m1_metrics.get("beam"),
    "grpo_greedy":  m1_metrics.get("grpo_greedy"),
    "grpo_beam":    m1_metrics.get("grpo_beam"),
}).style.background_gradient(cmap="Greens", axis=None).format("{:.4f}", na_rep="—"))
m1_preds = json.loads((RUN_DIR_M1 / "predictions_test.json").read_text(encoding="utf-8"))
plot_qualitative_samples(
    {"CE": m1_preds["ce_beam"], "CE→GRPO": m1_preds["grpo_beam"]},
    loaders_m1.test_eval.dataset,
    preset=DATA_CFG.image.presets[CFG_M1["data"]["transform_preset"]],
    n=6, seed=0,
    title=f"Model 1 — {CFG_M1['run_name']} (CE vs CE→GRPO, beam)",
)

