## § 9 — Model 2 rationale
**Phase 3 (Model 2): ViT-B/16 (frozen) + GRU decoder with Bahdanau (additive) attention.**

Encoder, decoder cell type, hidden size, optimiser, schedule, label smoothing, dropout — all identical to Phase 2. The only change: Luong → Bahdanau additive scoring, $\text{score}(h_t, \bar h_s) = v_a^\top \tanh(W_a [h_t; \bar h_s])$, which adds an MLP and ~$d_h \cdot d_a$ extra parameters. The controlled S5-M1 vs. S5-M2 pair answers *does the additional MLP capacity in additive attention pay off when every other variable is held constant?*

CFG_M2 = yaml.safe_load(Path("configs/models/s5_m2_vit_gru_bahdanau.yaml").read_text(encoding="utf-8"))
RUN_DIR_M2 = Path("outputs") / CFG_M2["run_name"]
RUN_DIR_M2.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
(RUN_DIR_M2 / "config.yaml").write_text(yaml.safe_dump(CFG_M2), encoding="utf-8")

if CFG_M2["data"]["transform_preset"] != CFG_M1["data"]["transform_preset"]:
    print(f"Model 2 uses transform '{CFG_M2['data']['transform_preset']}' — rebuilding loaders")
    loaders_m2 = DataLoaders.from_config(CFG_M2, DATA_CFG, DEVICE)
else:
    loaders_m2 = loaders_m1

model_m2 = build_captioner(CFG_M2, vocab).to(DEVICE)
print(f"Model 2 ({CFG_M2['run_name']})")
print(f"  trainable / total params: "
      f"{count_parameters(model_m2, True)/1e6:.2f}M / {count_parameters(model_m2, False)/1e6:.2f}M")

display(parameter_breakdown_table(model_m2).style
        .background_gradient(subset=["trainable_M"], cmap="Blues")
        .format({"params_M": "{:.3f}", "trainable_M": "{:.3f}", "trainable_%": "{:.1f}"}))
display(hyperparameter_summary_table(CFG_M2))
